        <headline>Heat Advisory issued June 21 at 2:59AM EDT until June 22 at 8:00PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...For the Heat Advisory, heat index values between 100 and
103 degrees expected. For the Extreme Heat Warning, dangerously
hot conditions with heat index values between 105 and 110 degrees
expected.

* WHERE...In Connecticut, Southern Litchfield County. In New York,
Dutchess and Eastern Ulster Counties.

* WHEN...For the Heat Advisory, from 11 AM to 8 PM EDT Sunday. For
the Extreme Heat Warning, from 11 AM Monday to 8 PM EDT Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Heat related illnesses increase significantly during
extreme heat and high humidity events. Hot temperatures and high
humidity may cause heat illnesses.
</description>
        <instruction>Drink plenty of fluids, stay in an air-conditioned room, stay out of
the sun, and check up on relatives and neighbors.</instruction>
